---
description: 'ENFORCE accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1 AA minimum)'
globs: *.astro, *.html
---

## Context

- Accessibility is essential to allow all users to access content
- Respect WCAG 2.1 level AA minimum standards
- Regularly test with accessibility tools and screen readers

## Semantic HTML

Always use appropriate semantic HTML tags:

```astro
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<header>
  <nav aria-label="Main navigation">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>

<main>
  <article>
    <h1>Article Title</h1>
    <section>
      <h2>Subsection</h2>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>

<footer>
  <p>Copyright 2024</p>
</footer>

<!-- ❌ AVOID -->
<div class="header">
  <div class="nav">
    <div class="link">Home</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Images

Always include descriptive `alt` attributes:

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD
---

<Image
  src="/logo.png"
  alt="Company logo"
  width={200}
  height={100}
/>

<img
  src="/decorative.png"
  alt=""
  role="presentation"
/>

<!-- ❌ AVOID -->
<img src="/image.jpg" />
```

Rules for `alt`:

- **Descriptive** for informative images: describe content or function
- **Empty (`alt=""`)** for decorative images with `role="presentation"`
- **Short and precise**: maximum 125 characters recommended
- Avoid "image of...", "photo of..." (redundant)

## Forms

Always associate labels with inputs:

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD
---

<form>
  <div>
    <label for="email">Email</label>
    <input
      type="email"
      id="email"
      name="email"
      required
      aria-describedby="email-error"
    />
    <span id="email-error" role="alert" class="error-message">
      {error}
    </span>
  </div>

  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<!-- ✅ Alternative with wrapping label -->
<label>
  <span>Email</span>
  <input type="email" name="email" required />
</label>
```

Rules:

- Always use `<label>` with `for` matching input `id`
- Use `aria-describedby` to link error messages
- Use `role="alert"` for important errors
- Use `required` for mandatory fields
- Provide clear and accessible error messages

## Color Contrast

Ensure sufficient contrast:

- **Normal text**: minimum contrast ratio 4.5:1 (WCAG AA)
- **Large text (18pt+)**: minimum contrast ratio 3:1 (WCAG AA)
- **Important text**: contrast ratio 7:1 recommended (WCAG AAA)

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD - Sufficient contrast
---

<p class="text-gray-900 bg-white">Readable text</p>
<p class="text-gray-600 bg-white">Secondary text</p>

<!-- ❌ AVOID - Insufficient contrast -->
<p class="text-gray-400 bg-gray-300">Hard to read text</p>
```

Use tools like [WebAIM Contrast Checker](https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/) to verify.

## Keyboard Navigation

Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible:

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD
---

<button type="button" class="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500">
  Click
</button>

<a href="/page" class="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500">
  Link
</a>

<!-- For non-interactive clickable elements -->
<div
  role="button"
  tabindex="0"
  class="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
  onkeydown={(e) => e.key === 'Enter' && handleClick()}
>
  Custom action
</div>
```

Rules:

- All interactive elements must be accessible with Tab
- Focus must be visible (use `focus:ring` or `focus:outline`)
- Tab order must be logical
- Avoid `tabindex` greater than 0 (except exceptional cases)

## ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications)

Use ARIA appropriately:

```astro
---
// ✅ GOOD
---

<!-- Navigation with ARIA -->
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
  <ul role="list">
    <li><a href="/" aria-current="page">Home</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<!-- Button with description -->
<button
  aria-label="Close menu"
  aria-expanded="false"
>
  ×
</button>

<!-- Dynamic content -->
<div
  role="alert"
  aria-live="polite"
  aria-atomic="true"
>
  {message}
</div>

<!-- Form with errors -->
<input
  type="email"
  aria-invalid={hasError}
  aria-describedby="email-error"
/>
<span id="email-error" role="alert">
  {errorMessage}
</span>
```

Common ARIA attributes:

- `aria-label`: Accessible label when visible text is not sufficient
- `aria-labelledby`: Reference to an element that serves as label
- `aria-describedby`: Reference to an element that describes
- `aria-live`: For regions that change dynamically ("polite" or "assertive")
- `aria-expanded`: For elements that open/close (true/false)
- `aria-hidden`: To hide decorative elements from screen readers
- `role`: Define the semantic role of an element

## Skip Links

Add a link to skip navigation:

```astro
---
// src/components/SkipLink.astro
---

<a
  href="#main-content"
  class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-blue-600 focus:text-white"
>
  Skip to main content
</a>

<main id="main-content">
  <!-- Main content -->
</main>
```

## Accessibility Testing

Always test:

1. **Keyboard navigation**: Use only Tab, Enter, Space
2. **Screen reader**: Test with NVDA (Windows) or VoiceOver (Mac)
3. **Automated tools**:
   - Lighthouse (Chrome DevTools)
   - axe DevTools extension
   - WAVE browser extension
4. **HTML validation**: Use W3C validator
5. **Contrast**: Use WebAIM Contrast Checker

## Important Rules

1. ✅ Use semantic HTML5 tags
2. ✅ Always add descriptive `alt` attributes to images
3. ✅ Ensure sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 minimum)
4. ✅ Associate labels with inputs using `for`/`id`
5. ✅ Handle visible keyboard focus
6. ✅ Use ARIA appropriately (don't overuse)
7. ✅ Test with screen readers
8. ✅ Provide accessible error messages
9. ✅ Ensure tab order is logical
10. ✅ Avoid animations that can cause problems (consider `prefers-reduced-motion`)

## Complete Example of an Accessible Component

```astro
---
type ButtonProps = {
  label: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
  disabled?: boolean;
  ariaLabel?: string;
}

export function AccessibleButton(props: ButtonProps) {
  return {};
}

const {} = AccessibleButton(Astro.props);
---

<button
  type="button"
  class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
  disabled={Astro.props.disabled}
  aria-label={Astro.props.ariaLabel || Astro.props.label}
  onclick={Astro.props.onClick}
>
  {Astro.props.label}
</button>
```
